args: Oh, hey, Aldred.\nWhy're you eating over here?
I prefer to dine in peace and quiet.
Gotcha. Come to think of it,\nI haven't eaten yet today, either.\nI was way too engrossed in my training.
Care to join me for a bite?
Together? Like, you and me? Hah!\nHard pass. Good one, though.
Well first off, why do you want to eat\ntogether in the first place?
Because we're friends.\nIs that so strange?
Get lost. I'm not here to\nplay buddy-buddy with you!
H-hey, there's no need to get mad.
Tch. Maybe try thinking\nbefore you speak next time.
I guess I made him angry.\nWhat did I do wrong?
I know I'm asking a lot,\nbut please, forgive Aldred.
There's nothing to forgive.\nI was the one who made him mad.
I hate to say it, but I think your mere\npresence set him off.
You know that he was fused with a dragon\nin the Syndicate's experiments, right?
Yeah. It was part of a project to artificially\ncreate people that can shapeshift, right?
I can't believe they were trying to replicate\na divine contract in such an abhorrent way.
Aldred was a product of the\nSynthetic Shapeshifting Project.
But he couldn't completely control\nthe dragon's power, so they deemed\nhim a failure.
What?! You can't just call\na person a ＂failure＂!
Agreed. And even though Aldred never\nshows it, he's deeply traumatized.\nThat's why when you... Well...
Tell me. What did I do wrong?

The Synthetic Shapeshifting Project's
ultimate goal was to create someone
who could transform into multiple
dragons.
Yes. The project's ultimate\naim was to emulate you,\n{player_name}.
Aldred has internalized the idea that\nthey saw him as a failed version of you.
Of course, none of this is your fault,\n{player_name}.
I just want you to understand\nhow complicated his feelings are.
Wha— A-Aldred!\nHave you been there this whole time?
I saw you with him, so I figured you might\nbe running your mouth. Guess I was right.
B-but I was only trying to explain how—
Rrrgh! And what about MY feelings?!
H-hey, let's all take a deep breath.
The damage is already done.\nMaybe you'll understand now,\n{player_name}.
Obeying you would mean\nacknowledging you as superior.\nIn other words...
It would mean admitting that the\nSyndicate was right—that I'm a ＂failure.＂
Chumming it up with you is more\nor less the same as admitting defeat.\nAnd I am NOT about to let that happen.
What are you talking about, Aldred?\nBeing my friend doesn't make you\nless than me in any way.
Say whatever you want.\nYou won't win me over.
...Okay. I understand.\nThen I take back what I said\nabout us being friends.
Finally. That's the first sensible thing\nyou've said all day. Now, get—
No, Aldred. Because you're right.\nWe're not friends. We're rivals.
You don't want to lose to me? Fine. But\nI don't plan on giving up that easily, either.
Ergo, we're rivals. Is that not\nthe definition of the word?
Fine. But get this through your thick skull:\nI won't lose to you. Not now, not ever.
I could say the same to you!
